15 CRIMES AGAINST MINORS.
16
17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
18
19 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code § 5-27-601(1), concerning the definition of
20 "child" as it applies to computer crimes against minors, is amended to read
21 as follows:
22 (1) “Child” means any person under seventeen (17) eighteen (18)
23 years of age;
24
25 SECTION 2. Arkansas Code § 5-27-602(c), concerning an affirmative
26 defense to prosecution for distributing, possessing, or viewing of matter
27 depicting sexually explicit conduct involving a child, is amended to read as
28 follows:
29 (c) It is an affirmative defense to a prosecution under this section
30 that the defendant in good faith reasonably believed that the person depicted
31 in the matter was seventeen (17) eighteen (18) years of age or older.
32
33 SECTION 3. Arkansas Code § 5-27-607 is amended to read as follows:
34 5-27-607. Determination of age of person.
35 (a) For purposes of this subchapter, the state must prove beyond a
36 reasonable doubt that a person who is depicted as or presents the appearance
